PURPOSE: To determine the 2-year incremental cost effectiveness of initial 
pramipexole treatment compared with initial levodopa treatment in patients with 
early Parkinson's disease (PD).
METHODS: 301 subjects with early PD were randomized to either pramipexole or 
levodopa and followed every 3 months over a 2-year period. Costs were assigned 
to patient collected health utilization data using a variety of methods. Health 
state preferences were estimated using the EuroQol.
RESULTS: Pramipexole strategy was an estimated 2,138 dollars (SE = 1,182 
