Unfinished symphony: a tribute to the life and career of Bernie O'Brien 
(1959-2004).

Briggs A(1), Buxton M, Drummond M, Goeree R, Sculpher MJ, Willan AR.

Author information:
(1)Centre for Health Economics, University of York, Heslington, York, United 
Kingdom.

The death of Bernie O'Brien in February 2004 brought a premature end to one of 
the most productive and influential careers in the area of health technology 
assessment and economic evaluation. A long-term member of the Society for 
Medical Decision Making, Bernie will be remembered for his research 
contributions in areas including outcome valuation, decision modeling, 
statistical methods in economic evaluation, and applied cost-effectiveness 
studies. He was also an excellent communicator and teacher and, above all, a fun 
guy to work with. In this article, the authors provide a review of Bernie's 
academic contributions.

